      "content": "sounds good, but we're really tight on time and the async stuff is making the current tests super flaky... like, half the time the test tries to click the checkout button before the page even finishes loading and it just crashes the whole build. \n\ncan you just write the actual Playwright/Cypress scripts now? and please make sure they are robust enough that they don't flake out and fail the build, otherwise the manager is gonna lose it if we don't get a green light on the next run.",
